packets.cmd

Class Cmd

  • java.lang.Object
    • packets.cmd.Cmd

  • public final class Cmd
extends java.lang.Object
    FULLY DOCUMENTED. There is an instance of this class for each command that any App can execute, as defined in each's App Profile. An instance of this class has a CcsdsCmdPkt, which it updates and sends when parameters are input by the user.
    Author:
    David McComas

    • Constructor Detail

      • Cmd

        public Cmd(java.lang.String Name,
   int MsgId,
   int FuncCode,
   int DataLen)
        Creates a Cmd with the input name, cmdmid, command code, and parameter byte length. Creates a CcsdsPkt for it.
        Parameters:
        Name - The name of this Cmd, to appear in the GUI.
        MsgId - The command message ID of it's parent App.
        FuncCode - The command code of this command. The index of the command in the App's list of commands.
        DataLen - The amount of bytes the parameters occupy.

        Parameters:
        paramValues - The values that are input by the user for each parameter.

      • addParam

        public final void addParam(CmdParam Param)
        Tells the Cmd to expect a parameter later with particular attributes, which are enclosed in the input CmdParam. This is NOT called every time a command is sent.
        Parameters:
        Param - The parameter that is required for this Cmd to be sent.
